# 9. The Structural Observation

Three quantities, all from the same S² geometry:

α × ln(m_Pl/m_e) = 3/8   (one-loop formula, 0.27% from exact)

β₂/β₁ = (18π+32)/(9π²) / (8/3) ≈ 1 × 3/8   (two-loop ratio, 0.31% from 3/8)

α* = −24π²/(18π+32) ≈ −8/3   (UV fixed point)

All three expressions involve 3/8, π, and the same geometric factors. The DST framework governs multiple levels of the theory through a single geometric structure: the S² solid angle (giving 4π), the SU(2) coherent state overlap (giving ½), and the Dirac loop factor (giving 4/3). The 3/8 is not a coincidence appearing at different levels — it is the geometric ratio 2π/((4/3)(4π)) propagating through the theory at every order.

**β₂_DST = 2/π + 32/(9π²)**

*The two-loop beta function of displacement spacetime, derived from spin-1/2 SU(2) geometry on S². No free parameters. The 3/8 is in the loops, not just the coupling.*

